name: Novak Djokovic
summary: In a startling incident at the Italian Open, tennis star Novak Djokovic was accidentally struck in the head by a water bottle thrown from the stands. The metal bottle caused discomfort, with Djokovic reporting nausea and dizziness. Despite the setback, Djokovic initially said he was "fine," though subsequent reports indicated he was recovering from the impact. The incident highlighted the vulnerability of players, underscoring the close proximity between fans and athletes. Despite the setback, Djokovic remained composed and went on to compete in the match, ultimately losing to Alejandro Tabilo.

name: Vladimir Putin
summary: Russia's President Vladimir Putin has officially begun his fifth term in office, with a grand ceremony held in the Kremlin. The inauguration marks a record-breaking achievement for Putin, who has now spent 24 years in power. As he embarks on his new six-year term, Putin has emphasized the need to challenge the West and highlighted his firm grip on Russia. The ceremony comes amidst heightened tensions between Russia and the United States, with recent events such as the Victory Day parade showcasing Putin's nuclear capabilities. The inauguration was attended by Prime Minister Mikhail Mishustin, who has been reappointed to his position.

name: Northern Lights Seattle
summary: Residents of the Seattle area were treated to a spectacular display of the aurora borealis on Friday and Saturday nights due to a solar storm. The Northern Lights were visible across Western Washington, with many observers capturing stunning images and video. The solar storm also caused the Northern Lights to be visible in other parts of the United States, including New York, Maine, and Michigan. Experts say that the geomagnetic storms responsible for the aurora are expected to continue, offering the potential for more Northern Lights displays in the coming nights.
